caption: I've been to this place twice, this making my third time and I think I'll retire from visiting here. I came here to celebrate my best friend's birthday and I am happy she enjoyed it. The Pretzel is absolutely delicious with the perfect amount of crisp on the outside and a soft texture on the inside. I ordered the Carnitas Quesadilla and although it was tasty, it was hard to eat with the excessive amount of grease and oil that oozed out and coated my fingers. Our table was in the corner so I think we were forgotten because, our water was never refilled and our plates we had for appetizers were never removed so we stacked them together and pushed them aside. The margaritas were so disappointing and tasted like pure margarita mix with 0 alcohol. There are no mirrors in the restrooms and I have no idea why this is a mystery but overall, friendly staff and lively atmosphere.

When I went, dozens of people were waiting outside and almost no one was getting their food. After waiting for half an hour (and being told that things were slightly behind), they then said to come back at 7. Not ideal, given that we had a reservation for before the game, but we then went back. Still no food. We never got it. It was an absolute mess there. No one apologized or tried to explain anything. I understand they were busy but that’s the point of an advance order.

Came here the other day to watch the fight. The hostess (Ashley) let us know she could not seat us in the main area of the restaurant because of the busy day ahead. Okay....  The restaurant had 6 other patrons in the whole establishment and she just sat a couple ahead of us. And by law you can only have 25% indoor capacity so I’m not sure why it would have been a problem to seat us.  We were out in the back, in a very dark area by the kitchen and storage.  The hostess had a mean demeanor to her and seemed to be have a power trip telling us where to sit. She also didn’t allow us to use the bathroom on the main side.  I felt I was being “segregated” - hard to say for sure if it’s because it was the color of my skin, or maybe because my gf is Chinese. But I sure did feel very uncomfortable. We ended up leaving after one beer.

Wanted to watch the UFC fight, but me And my boyfriend were not allowed to be seated on the main floor because it was “too crowded” despite there only being two other parties in the whole restaurant on the main floor who happened to be Caucasian. After we were seated behind a WALL in the far back by the kitchen, I walked Towards the main floor to use the restroom. The hostess ASHLEY physically blocked me from walking to the bathroom where customers go, and said “you can go on your side” in the back where the kitchen is. Sad that a poc employee would treat paying minority customers this way. Will not be returning. Hope her behavior is reprimanded.

I recently ordered here for pickup and my entire order was done and prepared poorly. It was missing chicken that was suppose to be apart of my salad, the sauces for the wings I ordered came on the side along with the sour cream for the potato skins. The menu gives you an option for this, however I choose to not have it on the side. Due to everything being on the side and the missing portion of the meal. I called to speak to someone about it. I was then told I was speaking to the manager Jennifer, I'm told her name was. After sharing my order number with her, she acknowledge the missing chicken almost immediately which tells me perhaps the kitchen saw the chicken that was suppose to be part of the meal sitting somewhere getting cold, however she begin to place blame on the way my order was done on the fact they never receive it, it goes straight to the kitchen, as if that matters. I informed her that its a big inconvenience to have to sit in my home and finish preparing a meal that I paid to be done properly. Literally I was shaking chicken together to season it the way I thought I was getting it. She told me it wasn't done incorrectly, that although it gives you an option to place things on the side, it will be done that way regardless due to what I ordered. Which doesn't make sense, its misleading to pretend like I have an option on how I want things to be done with my food. She then asked what I would like to be done and I told her I do not think I should pay fully for a meal that was not done the way I wanted, she got a bit bothered and begin to tell me it wasn't anything wrong with my meal besides the missing chicken and that the restaurant was busy (it was not I just left there). Restaurants are not that busy due to the current climate of nyc. She told me if I have an issue to go the website and complain and hung up the phone on me. Lets just say I will not be returning there, if you treat pickups this way, how do you treat the people dining in. I guess the same way because prior to me speaking to her, she was dealing with a check issue with a table at the restaurant, that might have been the busy part she was referring to. To have someone argue with you that their meal is not wrong even though they can see it was not done the way you choose is absurd to me and her attitude and the hanging up, egregious.

We came in to watch the last part of a football game when a waiter approached with a smug look (you know the type) assuming we wouldn't order anything. We weren't planning on ordering as we were caught up in the game. But, we don't care, we'll order drinks. But his approach was so arrogant that me and my gf audibly laughed (almost thinking it was a joke). So my gf ordered a drink and he looked at me demanding that I drink too. At this point no sensible person is going to order from this guy. We brought his arrogance to his attention and of course he had adorable comebacks. Once we left he changed all the televisions playing the game we were watching to another channel- just in case we'd try and watch from outside. Honestly, it made our night. It was in the top 5 most comical interactions I've had in NYC in 17 years. It will be the story me and my gf will tell at our respective places of business at the water cooler Monday morning about the waiter at Croxley's in Brooklyn.

Croxleys is hands down an awesome spot. I've never seen a "sports bar/wing spot" with such great food complimented by an incredible beer selection. They have a pamphlet that front and back probably has about 100 beers on it with a bit of everything from Belgian Trippels, Stouts and Porters, brown ales, and IPA's to pilsners and wheat ales. You name it and they've probably got it or something similar. They have great deals on wings at $.60 a wing and they are very good. The prices have steadily been increasing probably due to the offseason but this is still a good deal. Overall I find this an amazing spot and would highly recommend it.
